I also move and wiggle as I try on clothes before I buy it lol it took me a while to figure out what looks good on me and what to avoid. for shirts I'd lift both arms, if I can see a bit of stomach skin it's a no. also bend over to see if the shirt doesn't reveal too much boob/bra. wear a favorite bra/color and check what fabrics best suit your curves and bra. sometimes a fabric can be too thin and can show the outline/color of the bra. jeans, it has to feel comfortable enough to sit for at least 1 hour. it can look cute as you're standing but sitting with discomfort isn't cute. also try to rise your leg at your max and if you can't lift it half way as you're trying on the jean it's too tight. pants/leggings, underwear outline is what sticks out the most and still gives me a headache. even if you wear the thinnest or v shaped underwear somehow it still shows something. but something to notice is if your bending down and the pants/leggings lower down it might be small, try a size up. sitting can also help you with something that bothered me, with leggings as I sit the waist part can curl down and when I stand up it can be a bit obvious and having to adjust everytime I get up can be annoying. I'm a fan of high waist leggings.
